Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with multi-robot missions and their fault tolerance. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Behavior Trees for controlling the robots. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with controlling a system of multiple robots. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is relevant as the paper deals with a system of multiple agents (robots) working together. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also possible as the paper discusses the extension of a single robot system to a multi-robot system using Behavior Trees.
